    "title": "New Boiler Cost 2026: Installation Prices & What to Expect",
    "slug": "new-boiler-cost-2026-installation-prices",
    "excerpt": "How much does a new boiler cost in 2026? Complete price breakdown for combi, system, and regular boilers, plus installation costs and running expenses.",
    "date": "2026-01-22",
    "category": "Cost Guides",
    "author": "TradeHub",
    "readTime": "8 min read",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Installing a new boiler is a significant investment, typically costing £1,500-£3,500 including fitting. But prices vary widely depending on boiler type, size, brand, and installation complexity. Here's your complete 2026 price guide."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Boiler Costs by Type"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Combi boilers (most popular for UK homes): £800-£2,500 for the boiler, £1,500-£3,000 including installation. System boilers (for homes with higher hot water demand): £900-£2,800 for the boiler, £1,800-£3,500 including installation. Regular/conventional boilers (for larger properties with existing tanks): £1,000-£2,500 for the boiler, £2,000-£4,000 including installation."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Combi boilers are cheapest to install because they don't require separate hot water cylinders or cold water tanks. They're ideal for small to medium homes with 1-2 bathrooms."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Installation Costs Breakdown"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "The installation labour typically costs £500-£1,000 depending on: Job complexity (like-for-like replacement is cheapest), boiler location (moving it adds £300-£800), system upgrades (new pipework, radiators, or controls add £200-£1,500), flue changes (£150-£400 if the flue needs relocating), time required (most installations take 1-3 days)."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "A straightforward like-for-like combi boiler replacement in the same location typically takes 1 day and costs £1,500-£2,200 including a mid-range boiler. Converting from a regular boiler to a combi requires removing tanks and modifying pipework, taking 2-3 days and costing £2,500-£4,000+."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Boiler Brands and Price Ranges"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Budget brands (£800-£1,200): Ideal, Baxi, Potterton — reliable, 5-7 year warranties, good for rental properties or budget installations. Mid-range brands (£1,200-£2,000): Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Viessmann — excellent reliability, 7-10 year warranties, best value for most homeowners. Premium brands (£2,000-£3,000+): Viessmann Vitodens, high-efficiency models — 10-12 year warranties, highest efficiency ratings, best for large homes or long-term investment."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Worcester Bosch is the UK's most popular brand, known for reliability and good customer service. Their Greenstar range offers excellent efficiency at mid-range prices."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "What Size Boiler Do You Need?"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Combi boiler output is measured in kW. Choosing the right size is crucial: 24-28kW: 1-2 bedroom flat or small house, 1 bathroom. 28-34kW: 2-3 bedroom house, 1-2 bathrooms. 35-42kW: 3-4 bedroom house, 2-3 bathrooms, higher hot water demand."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "An oversized boiler wastes energy and costs more. An undersized boiler won't provide enough hot water. A Gas Safe engineer will calculate the correct size during a survey."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Additional Costs to Consider"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Beyond the boiler and basic installation, budget for: Magnetic filter (£100-£150, highly recommended to protect the new boiler from sludge). System flush (£300-£500, essential if replacing an old boiler to remove debris). Upgraded controls (£150-£300 for smart thermostats like Hive or Nest). Radiator upgrades (£80-£300 per radiator if needed). Asbestos removal (£500-£1,500 if found around old boiler — only in pre-1999 homes). Scaffolding (£400-£800 if needed for external flue work)."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Running Costs and Energy Savings"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Modern A-rated boilers are 90%+ efficient, compared to 60-70% for boilers over 15 years old. Replacing an old boiler can save £300-£500 per year on energy bills. The payback period for a new boiler is typically 5-8 years through energy savings alone."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Condensing boilers (all new boilers must be condensing) recover heat from waste gases, achieving 90-95% efficiency. Combined with smart controls and good insulation, you can reduce heating costs by 30-40%."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Boiler Warranties and Servicing"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Most boiler warranties require annual servicing to remain valid. Budget £80-£100 per year for a service. Many manufacturers offer extended warranties (up to 12 years) if installed by an approved installer — ask your Gas Safe engineer about this."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Annual servicing is essential for safety, efficiency, and warranty compliance. Boilers without servicing records lose significant resale value and can fail prematurely."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Finance Options for New Boilers"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Many installers offer finance: 0% APR for 12-24 months (typical for purchases over £1,000). Low-interest loans spread over 3-5 years. Boiler grants (up to £7,500 for eligible low-income households via ECO4 scheme)."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Always check the total cost of finance — 'interest-free' deals sometimes inflate the boiler price. Compare the cash price with the financed total."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "Get Quotes from Gas Safe Engineers"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Always get 2-3 quotes from Gas Safe registered engineers. Ensure quotes include: boiler model and size, all installation work, materials (pipes, flue, fittings), system flush and filter, VAT, warranty details."
